Author: StreamSpace
Title: [ANN] [ICO] StreamSpace - ICO Has Ended
Body: The StreamSpace ICO has concluded.  Thank you for your support during the StreamSpace Token Sale!    Now that the sale has concluded, we would like to provide you with some details. A total of 721 contributors purchased 74,713,414.72  StreamShares (SSH). At current market rates of ETH and BTC, this totals $2,997,960.93.  Any supporters who contributed in USD or BTC must email us at ico@stream.space with their ETH address to receive SSH. This email must come from the same email you used to register for the sale. The deadline for sending your ETH address is Friday March 2nd, 2018 at 6pm CST.    If you contributed in ETH, tokens will be sent to the ETH address from which the contribution was sent unless you email us at ico@stream.space.    Note: Failure to provide us with a valid ETH address promptly could result in a loss of funds.    Tokens will be distributed by March 14, 2018.    Thank you for your patience as we handled most of the sale via manual processes. Because of this manual nature of the sale, we are happy to report that we faced zero exploited vulnerabilities and zero successful attacks.    In the coming weeks, StreamSpace will release another Tech Talk video and update the roadmap and white paper to reflect the outcome of this token sale.  StreamSpace is hosting the International Filmmaker Brunch and a Filmmaker Celebration at South by Southwest festival (SXSW) in Austin, Texas on March 10, 2018. Follow us on social media to stay up to date on other events.    We are beginning to hire additional developers, so be sure to follow our Indeed and Stack Overflow pages for more information on available roles.    We are incredibly excited for the opportunity to empower filmmakers and continue building our distributed streaming video on demand platform. Thank you to all of our supporters who made this token sale a success!

Author: S3cco
Title: [ANN] [ICO] StreamSpace - ICO Has Ended
Body: Bitcoin Garden: There’s now a streaming future for indie filmmakers https://bitcoingarden.org/theres-now-streaming-future-indie-filmmakers/  Streamed video on demand (SVOD) consumption has exploded in popularity. The figures speak from themselves. Netflix has 100 million paying subscribers and rising; Amazon Prime has 30 million; Hulu more than 25 million and if you want to look even further afield there’s the granddaddy of streamed video YouTube with one billion users.  By any measure, that presents a massive opportunity to a new entrant that can do things differently, not just for the sake of it, but to make the film industry work better for consumers and creators alike.  This is especially relevant when it comes to the position of independent filmmakers in the industry.  As we’ve seen, there are more channels for films to be seen through beyond network TV and the movie theatre, but has this led to a flourishing in the number and quality of the films being seen? Sadly, the answer is an emphatic no....

Author: streamspacerobert
Title: [ANN] [ICO] StreamSpace - ICO Has Ended

Author: StreamSpace
Title: [ANN] [ICO] StreamSpace - ICO Has Ended
Body: StreamSpace selected Proof of Stake Time (PoST) as the reward algorithm for StreamShares (SSH), the transactional token used for payment and access rights on the StreamSpace platform. PoST allows a poorer member with a smaller stake to have more strength if they are active and challenge a richer stakeholder who is less active in supporting the service. Granting more rewards to a committed underdog is akin to giving a weak team in American professional football the right to go first in the draft pick; proper choices will elevate a weak team against a dominant team that rests on its laurels and fails to keep developing new talent.
